des:
With the Toucan skill and alexa configuration, you can now interact with your Toucan Smart Sconce Light by voice to turn on/off, change color, color temperature and brightness. To get started, select the "Enable" button in the Toucan skill page from the Amazon Alexa app to link your Toucan application account and discover your device by saying "Alexa, discover devices". Once done, you can begin controlling your Toucan Smart Sconce Lights through Alexa.

Light Group
Create Toucan Smart Sconce Light group in the Toucan app to group your lights and control them together. For example: group multiple lights in living room by naming it as "Living Room".

Step by Step Guide:
(1). Download our "Toucan" app from Google Play or App Store;
(2). Launch the app and log in;
(3). Set up the connection with Toucan Smart Sconce Light by following the app instruction;
(4). Select one of the preset group names provided or create your own during connection setup which are editable at any time;
(5). Go to "Amazon Alexa" app;
(6). Go to Skills and search for "Toucan";
(7). Select "Enable" for the "Toucan" skill. Log in to your Toucan app account and authorize access to link your Toucan Sconce Light;
(8). Discover your device by talking to Echo "Alexa, discover my smart home devices" and your Toucan Smart Sconce Light should be found within 20s;
(9). All setup is complete and you can start to controlling your lights by voice with Alexa.

Light Control
Control multiple Toucan Smart Sconce Lights together by group name — for example by rooms
You can say the following:
- To turn light on or off, for example: "Alexa, turn on living room";
- To change the brightness by percentage, for example: "Alexa, brighten the living room by 80 percent";
- To change the light color, for example: "Alexa, set the living room light to red";
- To set the light color temperature: for example: "Alexa,make the living room warmer";
